    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="74"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <head>EXHIBIT T.</head>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">State of California</hi>, <hi rend="italic">City and County
                        of San Francisco:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Max Waizman, being first duly sworn, deposes and says: That he is a resident of
                    the city and county of San Francisco, State of California, and was, on the 2d
                    day of August, 1891, the sole owner of the American schooner <hi rend="italic"
                        >James Hamilton Lewis</hi>, and was on the 2d day of August, 1891, the date
                    of the seizure of said schooner, a citizen of the United States of America.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Max Waizman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">Subscribed and sworn to before me this <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1893-12-29">29th day of December, A. D.
                            1893</date>.</dateline>
                    <lb/>
                    <seg rendition="#left">[<hi rend="smallcaps">seal.</hi>]</seg>
                    <signed rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. S. Manley</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Commissioner U. S. Circuit Court, Northern District of
                            California.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
